A two- month-old baby from Bishop lavis is missing, the family and community continues with the search. Monique Mortlock has more. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - A desperate mother – and the Bishop Lavis community in Cape Town– are searching for a missing baby. Two-month-old Kai-isha Meniers was allegedly taken by an unknown woman on 30 April. Police have shared pictures of the suspect with the baby, taken from CCTV footage – requesting assistance from the public. On 30 April, pay-day weekend, unemployed Francis Meniers was hoping for a miracle. She met a woman who offered to help her while she had been standing with her two sons and two-month-old baby Kai-isha. READ: Mother reunited with baby after kidnapping So this seemingly good Samaritan bought Meniers diapers and food, all the while holding baby Kai-isha. The woman offered to watch Meniers’ children while she quickly popped into the supermarket. She began a frantic search but to no avail. Police and other safety structures got involved, in searching for the suspect and the baby, however, residents in the area say the SAPS has been of little assistance. The family says it will not stop searching until baby Kai-isha is safely at home. Watch the video above for more details on this story.